NETWORK ACCESS ACCEPTABLE USE POLICY: This Policy sets out the terms for the acceptable use of the Prison Network facilities and services. All people using the Network must comply with this Policy and the Acceptable Use policies any other networks or hosts used and must comply with all applicable laws. THE GEO GROUP AUSTRALIA PTY LTD (AND ITS ASSOCIATES) (“GEO”) MAKES NO REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES CONCERNING THE AVAILABILITY OR SECURITY OF THE NETWORK. ALL NETWORK USE IS PROVIDED ON AN AS-IS BASIS. BY USING THE NETWORK, YOU RELEASE, HOLD HARMLESS AND REIMBURSE GEO FOR ANY LOSSES OR DAMAGES THAT MAY RESULT IN ANY WAY FROM YOUR USE OF THE NETWORK. In addition, by using the Network you agree that GEO takes no responsibility and assumes no liability for any content uploaded, shared, transmitted, or downloaded by you or any person, or for anything you may encounter or any data that may be lost or compromised while connected to the Network. GEO reserves the right to disconnect any User at any time and for any reason. Users will not be given access to the GEO intranet or permission to install any software on GEO’s computers. Inappropriate use of the Network is not permitted and GEO may determine that a particular use is inappropriate at any time. While not an exhaustive list, the following are guidelines in considering whether inappropriate use has occurred:
Failure to respect the privacy and intellectual property rights of others. Failure to respect the integrity of the Network and any other public or private computing/network systems. Use of the Network for malicious or fraudulent purposes is prohibited. Use of the Network to post or forward abusive, offensive, harassing, insulting or discriminatory messages or images is prohibited. Use of the Network to preclude or hamper other User’s access to the Network or other any other networks is prohibited. Nothing may be installed or used that modifies, disrupts, or interferes in any way with service for any other user, host, or network.
CLICK HERE TO CONFIRM YOU AGREE TO THE ABOVE ACCEPTABLE USE POLICY
